Session: share system design + MCP server scaffold. Built the full share auth model in theTube-share — minted JWTs with embedded secrets, time-based SHA256 hashes (Shortcuts can hash natively), same verification path for all devices (Mac/phone/kids). Dropped the asymmetric key pair approach in favor of symmetric HMAC — simpler, one Lambda code path, Mac and phone have equivalent trust. Scripts: mint-token.sh (Keychain + Touch ID), share-request.sh, verify-local.sh (passing). Key decisions: JWT carries its own state (secret embedded in claims, no server-side store), scope claim for authorization, sub claim for device identity, ±30s timestamp window prevents replay, passkeys for browser write escalation, Cognito for public users coexists with minted tokens for owner devices. Also scaffolded theTube-mcp (read-only AWS access — CF logs, Lambda config, distribution behaviors). New blog posts: the-share-system (rewritten), aws-as-a-filesystem (new — /proc for the cloud via WebDAV over Lambda), mcp-log-reader (added SQLite state tracking). Three repos pushed: theTube-share, theTube-mcp, theTube-content. Next: wire CF function for /w/*?* → 202, connect MCP server to verify captures land in logs.
